# Architecture Audit Mode

## Living sync (default during implementation)

When the user edits code, **update affected audit documentation in the same task**:

1. Find the audit doc via [docs/audit/INDEX.md](docs/audit/INDEX.md).
2. Update only impacted sections per [docs/audit/MAINTENANCE.md](docs/audit/MAINTENANCE.md).
3. If the user cites `@audit path#section`, edit that section first.

Cross-cutting updates when relevant: `docs/audit/DUPLICATES.md`, `docs/audit/EXECUTION_TRACES.md`.

## Audit-only pass (explicit request)

When the user asks for an architecture **audit** (not a feature), follow [docs/todo/Architecture Audit Mode.md](docs/todo/Architecture Audit Mode.md):

- DO NOT modify application code.
- Document the code as it exists today.
- If uncertain: **Unknown from static analysis.**

## Standard README sections

Purpose, Files, Entry Points, Dependencies, Runtime Usage, Possible Dead Code, Notes, Per-file inventory, Execution traces.

Accuracy over speed in audit-only mode; surgical section updates in living sync mode.
